The paper discusses a new workflow for software development that utilizes dependently typed programming, which is a topic commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the differences in design, complexity, and provability of software, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties that can be expressed in a proof-driven development workflow, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computational Geometry).
